@startuml
' Configuration for a clean academic style
skinparam monochrome true
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor white
skinparam ActivityBorderColor black

title Kriging with External Drift (KED) Workflow

start

:**Inputs:**
1. Rain Data Points (x, y, P_obs)
2. Digital Elevation Model (Z_grid);

:**1. Drift Estimation**
Extract elevation (Z) at station coordinates;
:Fit Linear Regression Model:
P_trend = α + β * Z;

split
    :**2. Residual Calculation**
    Subtract trend from observed points:
    R(s_i) = P_obs(s_i) - P_trend(s_i);
    
    :**3. Variogram Modeling**
    Fit theoretical variogram to residuals
    (e.g., Spherical, Gaussian);
    
    :**4. Ordinary Kriging**
    Interpolate residuals over the entire DEM grid
    → **R_krige(x, y)**;
split again
    :**Grid Trend Application**
    Apply regression model to the entire DEM:
    → **Trend(x, y) = α + β * Z(x, y)**;
end split

:**5. Final Reconstruction**
Add Kriged residual surface and elevation trend:
P_final(x, y) = R_krige(x, y) + Trend(x, y);

:**Output:**
Final Interpolated Rainfall Grid;

stop
@enduml